revision.text:
{{Infobox language |name=Burate |nativename= |region=[[Indonesia]]n [[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]] |speakers=100 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[East Geelvink Bay languages|East Geelvink Bay]]? |fam2= |iso3=bti |glotto=bura1276 |glottorefname=Burate }} '''Burate''' is a [[Papuan language]] of the [[Indonesia]]n province of [[Papua (province)|Papua]], on the eastern shore of [[Cenderawasih Bay]]. The specific areas that the Burate language is spoken in include the [[Papua (province)|Papua Provence]], the [[Wapoga River|Wapoga river]] mouth, one village of the [[Waropen Regency|Waropen Bawah]] subdistrict, and the [[Yapen Islands Regency|Yapen Waropen]] regency.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.verbix.com/maps/language/Burate.html|title=Where on earth do they speak Burate?|website=www.verbix.com|language=en|access-date=2017-02-08}}</ref>
Burate is lexically similar to the [[East Geelvink Bay languages]] and presumably belongs in that family, but is too poorly attested to be sure.
