{{Infobox language |name=Mzieme |nativename=Northern Zeme |region=[[Nagaland]] |speakers=29,000 |date=1997 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Zeme languages]] |iso3=nme |glotto=mzie1235 |glottorefname=Mzieme Naga }}
'''Mzieme''' is a [[Sino-Tibetan languages|Sino-Tibetan]] language spoken in India. It has been called '''Northern Zeme''' due to its lack of official recognition, but is not particularly close to [[Zeme language|Zeme]].
Mzieme is spoken to the northeast of Zeme in [[Peren district]], southeastern [[Nagaland]], as well as in [[Senapati district]], [[Manipur]].
