'''Touhfat Mouhtare''' is a [[Comoros|Comorian]] writer.
Born in Comoros, Mouhtare has lived in various countries in Africa, and studied in France,<ref name="uwa.edu.au">{{cite web|url=http://aflit.arts.uwa.edu.au/mouhtare_ames.html|title=Touhfat Mouhtare|publisher=|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.africine.org/?menu=fiche&no=30065|title=Africiné|publisher=|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> where she received a diploma in foreign languages from the [[Sorbonne]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coelacanthe.oxatis.com/PBBios.asp?ItmID=10210|title=Touhfat Mouhtare|publisher=|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> She is the second published Comorian woman prose writer, after [[Coralie Frei]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coelacanthe.oxatis.com/PBHotNews.asp?ItmID=137671|title=Touhfat Mouhtare, une voix de femme et des promesses|publisher=|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> and has written poetry as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.loumeto.com/mes-lectures/article/touhfat-mouhtare-une-poetesse-des|title=Touhfat MOUHTARE, une poétesse deS AfriqueS - Espace Dridjo|publisher=|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> ''Ames suspendues'', a collection of [[novella]]s, was published in 2011.<ref name="uwa.edu.au"/> She has also published articles on various subjects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://terangaweb.com/author/touhfat/|title=Touhfat Mouhtare, Auteur à Terangaweb - L'Afrique des idées|publisher=|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref>
