'''Zeynelabidîn Zinar''' (born 1953) is a [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] writer and researcher.<ref name="Suleiman1996">{{cite book|last=Suleiman|first=Yasir|title=Language and identity in the Middle East and North Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1stXcN-v0JUC&pg=PA162|accessdate=20 December 2010|year=1996|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-0-7007-0410-1|page=162}}</ref> He was born in the village of [[Hedhedk]] in the district of [[Beşiri]] in 1953. He has been one of the main figures in the area of [[Kurdish language|Kurdish]] folklore. Moreover, he has changed many classical Kurdish texts from [[Arabic language|Arabic]] script to the Kurdish [[Latin]]-based script. Between 1986 and 2006, he has published around seventy books in the Kurdish language.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n2004-60776 Zinar, Zeynelabidin]. Accessed October 20, 2012.</ref> His main work is a ten volume book on the Kurdish folklore and oral traditions, called ''Xwençe''. It took him twelve years to complete this work, and its twelve volumes were published between 1989-1997 in [[Sweden]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://books.google.lt/books/about/Kurdistana_xwed%C3%AA_j%C3%AE_%C5%9Fewit%C3%AE.html?id=uFs8GQAACAAJ&redir_esc=y |title=Kurdish folktales collected by Z. Zinar, Zeynelabidin Zinar |publisher=Google Books}}</ref>

